{
  "texts": [
    "Taxonomy of deep learning techniques in computational mechanicsIn order to discuss the deep learning methods in a structured manner, we introduce the following taxonomy:• simulation substitution (Sect. 2)-data-driven modeling (Sect.",
    "2.1) -physics-informed learning (Sect. 2.2)• simulation enhancement (Sect.",
    "3)• discretizations as neural networks (Sect. 4)• generative approaches (Sect.",
    "5)• deep reinforcement learning (Sect. 6)Simulation substitution replaces the entire simulation with a surrogate model, which in the context of deep learning are deep neural networks (NNs).",
    "The model can be trained with supervised learning, which purely relies on labeled data and therefore is referred to as data-driven modeling.The generalization errors of these models can be reduced by physics-informed learning."
  ]
}